stanfordlogic.prover
Class Fact

java.lang.Object
  stanfordlogic.prover.Expression
      stanfordlogic.prover.Fact
Direct Known Subclasses:
GroundFact, VariableFact
public abstract class Fact
extends Expression

A fact is something true in a knowledge base. A fact has a relation name, followed by zero or more columns (parameters to the relation).

unify

public Substitution unify(Fact fact)
Attempt to unify this fact with fact. If the unification succeeds, return the substitution used -- but does not actually change the facts. If the unification fails, return null.

Note that before attempting to unify with fact, you probably want to make sure that the facts have unique variable names.

Parameters:
fact - The fact to unify with.
Returns:
The substitution used to unify these, or null.

fromExpression

public static Fact fromExpression(GdlExpression exp)
Construct a fact, ground or variable, from a GdlExpression. Returns a GroundFact if there were no variables in the GdlExpression, and a VariableFact otherwise.

Parameters:
exp - The expression from which to construct the fact.
Returns:
The fact constructed from GdlExpression exp.
